==Description==
[[File:LZ62.webp|300px|thumb|right|A photograph of Level 916|alt=LZ61]]
Level 916 is a vast collection of non-euclidean space composed of metalloids that radiates from the center to the periphery.

Externally, Level 916 resembles a parking lot covered in metal, however there are no vehicles parked it. Due to the metal cover, everything on the level is reflective, which makes the light extremely bright - which makes a visual threat to wanderers. Therefore, it is recommended that wanderers wear eye protection such as sunglasses, protective goggles, etc., before entering this level.

Environmentally, the temperature in Level 916 is never predictable . Regardless of its form, the temperature and heat within the level are uneven and random, so any object that wanderers encounter in their path may have extremely high temperatures - or conversely, touch an object with very low or no heat. In terms of atmospheric morphology and oxygen density, the regions tend to be secore and stable - unlike the well-known Environmentally Hazardous Level, [[Level 24]].

Level 916 does not contain any food items other than "Edible Chromium". There may be some food-shaped objects in Level 916 - but they are all made of pure metal. Edible Chromium is a small lumpy object packaged in chrome-colored paper, which is most different from metal substances in that it is soft. When wanderers attempt to pinch Edible Chromium, they will find that chromium is as soft and elastic as jelly. 4 boxes of edible chromium can provide energy that fits an adult's need for a day.

There may be a number of objects made of metal in Level 916, including the aforementioned metal foods, as well as some digital products and daily necessities. Due to their unusually hard nature, some objects have a high value in the Backrooms.

Level 916 has a distinctly millennial feel. The layout and interior layout of the rooms on the floor are similar to those of the 00s of the 21st century, presenting a retro-futuristic and metal-mechanical model, with furniture that shines with technological optimism. The high grayscale visuals and the silver plastic that mimicked the chrome finish were clean and shiny, and at one time fascinated many wanderers.

Among the rooms in Level 916, the Empty Rooms are the most common, followed by The Dense Rooms. Rarely, wanderers may encounter the Staircases and the PC Rooms.
===The Empty Room abbr.ER===
The Empty Rooms are the most common area in Level 916. As its name suggests, there is nothing here but metal-plated walls. The environment in the Empty Rooms are the most stable, as there are no other objects to concentrate the light on. Often, it is a good choice to camp in the Empty Rooms in Level 916, and wanderers also believe that the Empty Rooms may be the first area to be established in a sustainable community after the energy of Level 916 is used in the future.

===The Dense Room abbr.DR===
The Dense Room is a relatively rare area of Level 916, and has the opposite properties of the Empty Room, which is dotted with a large number of silver-like cylindrical cylinders. Due to their special design, the pillars in the room will often reflect light sources into several reinforcement points, causing the wanderer to deal the damage mentioned above.

===The Staircase===
[[File:LZ63.webp|300px|thumb|right|A photo of The Staircase. Taken by Chromecore Club.|alt=LZ61]]
The Staircase is an area with a significant ability to leave the level. When wanderers enter the Staircase, they will notice that the upper edge of the Staircase is fading and degrading to its normal wooden color. They may exit Level 916 in this room.

===The PC Room===
The PC Room is a small area that is secluded and may not even be thought to exist. It has been said that the the PC Room controls the style and environmental characteristics of objects in Level 916, but this is unconfirmed.


==Entity==
===Chromium===
[[File:Chromethings2.webp|300px|thumb|right|A photo of Chromium. It may resemble a chromium art from the Y2K period of the Frontrooms.|alt=LZ61]]
Chromium is a non-hazardous entity that exists in Level 916. Their appearances are similar to that of chrome objects in most levels, but one notable difference from them is that Chromium has a brighter appearance than chrome objects, and has all but the rest of the components - in other words, Chromium is more realistic than chrome objects.

Chromium may have the ability to communicate with wanderers, but this is obscured by the strong psychic effects of the level - wanderers are unable to tell if they are communicating with Chromium or if they are talking to themselves by a disturbed mind.

The rest of the properties of Chromium are currently unknown.

==Phenomena==
===Interference Phenomenon===
The Interference Phenomenon is a negative effect that exists within high-light levels and is visually and mentally harmful to wanderers. The reaction mechanism lies in the interference phenomenon produced by the high-intensity light source under the all-reflective mirror surface.

When multiple light sources are in non-parallel reflective surfaces, they may be enhanced in some areas and weakened in others due to superposition. When the light intensity of certain parts exceeds the threshold, excessive energy inclusion may cause irreversible damage to the wanderer's eyes, such as glaucoma, dispersion, and even blindness; When the light intensity of some parts is weakened or even canceled out, the dark environment may cause the wanderer to suffer from short-term sudden blindness caused by the difference in light potential, which will cause great physical and mental damage to the wanderer.

===Thermal Aberration Phenomenon===
Thermal Aberration Phenomenon is an unstable phenomenon that exists in an energy-enclosed space. When light is constantly reflected in the mirror, some parts of the light are superimposed to produce higher energy. This effect would normally cause parts of the level to be visually different from others, but this difference is significantly diminished due to the fact that Level 916 is composed entirely of chromium with a high melting point and hardness.

If a wanderer accidentally touches the area, their body parts may be burned or even melted as a result. Studies have shown that temperatures in some areas can reach as high as 1600°C under this effect.

==Anecdote==
===The 1st Y2k and the Metal Futurism Movement===
The 1st Y2k and the Metal Futurism Movement took place in Level 916 in 2016, 15 years after its discovery. Similar to the Chromium Core in the Frontrooms, Y2k, and Metal Heart Retro Movements, wanderers flock into Level 916 with an almost obsessive influx and collect chromium from Level 916.

It is considered to be a staged rebellion against backroom totalitarianism and entity cultism. People spontaneously feel nostalgic for the futurism that never came, and fantasize about the future of human industry and machinery. Amazingly, due to the asymmetrical circulation of information between the Frontrooms and the Backrooms, wanderers in the Backrooms are often unable to relate to outside metal-futurist activists, but in the end, both movements sparked a frenzy in the Frontrooms and Backrooms, respectively.

==Entrance and Exit==
[[File:Chromethings1.webp|200px|thumb|right|A mobile phone with a Chrome Attribute. It may have been produced in the millennium.|alt=LZ61]]
===Entrance===
*Noclipping through any door with metal properties may lead you here.
*If you pick up an object with chrome properties in any level, you can noclip to this level.
===Exits===
*If you choose to use a Chrome computer, you may end up in [[Level 1]].
*Noclipping through a light post sends one to [[Level 917]]
